<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Elevated living, strong schools and consistent capital growth in the inner north-east.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Wavell Heights sits about seven kilometres north-east of the CBD, with an elevated topography that gives the suburb a distinctive character relative to its flatter inner north neighbours. Bordered by Nundah to the south and Clayfield to the south-east, it occupies a position at the top of the inner north-east corridor where family buyers who want strong school catchments, an established residential atmosphere and consistent long-term growth consistently land after their broader search.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
